column1: #Text=Reconciliation rules for n-ary relations encoded in RDF triples

#Text=When citing tcn3r, please use the following reference:
#Text=Pierre Monnin, Miguel Couceiro, Amedeo Napoli, and Adrien Coulet.

column1: #Text=In: Ontologies and Concepts in Mind and Machine - 25th
#Text=International Conference on Conceptual Structures, ICCS 2020, Bolzano, Italy, September
#Text=Ed. by Mehwish Alam, Tanya Braun, and Bruno Yun.
#Text=  booktitle = {Ontologies and Concepts in Mind and Machine - 25th International Conference
#Text=               on Conceptual Structures, {ICCS} 2020, Bolzano, Italy, September 18-20,
#Text=Executes reconciliation rules on every pair of relationships in the triplestore.
#Text=tcn3r --configuration conf.json -o output.ttl --simlimit SL --complimit CL --dimensionlimit DL --max-rows MR -t threads
#Text=* *conf.json*: is the configuration file needed to configure the scripts -- see below
#Text=* *output.ttl*: is the path to the output TTL file where the generated links between relationships will be stored
#Text=* *SL*: Minimum similarity on non-empty aggregated dimensions to consider relations as related (< 0 to disable)
#Text=* *CL*: Minimum number of non-empty comparable aggregated dimensions to consider relations as related (< 0 to disable)
#Text=* *DL*: Minimum number of non-empty aggregated dimensions to apply simlimit or complimit (< 0 to disable)
#Text=* *MR*: Max number of rows the SPARQL endpoint can return for a query
#Text=* *threads*: number of threads to use when comparing relations (e.g., 8)
#Text=You can use the target ``run`` of the provided Makefile that calls the Docker image with:
#Text=The ``data`` subdirectory of the current directory is shared with the Docker container as ``/data``.
#Text=It is expected that the JSON configuration file is in this directory.
#Text=``/data`` is also the directory where the output TTL file will be stored.
#Text=``simlimit`` is set to 0.8, ``complimit`` to 2 and ``dimensionlimit`` is set to 2.
#Text=tcn3r --configuration conf.json -o output.ttl --simlimit SL --complimit CL --dimensionlimit DL --max-rows MR --explain true
#Text=* *conf.json*: is the configuration file needed to configure the scripts -- see below
#Text=* *output.txt*: is the path to the output text file where explanations of links between relationships will be stored
#Text=* *SL*: Minimum similarity on non-empty aggregated dimensions to consider relations as related (< 0 to disable)
#Text=* *CL*: Minimum number of non-empty comparable aggregated dimensions to consider relations as related (< 0 to disable)
#Text=* *DL*: Minimum number of non-empty aggregated dimensions to apply simlimit or complimit (< 0 to disable)
#Text=* *MR*: Max number of rows the SPARQL endpoint can return for a query
#Text=URIs of relations to compare will be asked interactively.
#Text=A configuration JSON file is needed to configure the scripts.
#Text=* _server-address_: address of the SPARQL endpoint to query
#Text=* _url-json-conf-attribute_: URL attribute to use to get JSON results
#Text=* _url-json-conf-value_: value of the _url-json-conf-attribute_ to get JSON results
#Text=* _url-default-graph-attribute_: URL attribute to use to define the default graph
#Text=* _url-default-graph-value_: value of _url-default-graph-attribute_ to define the default graph
#Text=* _url-query-attribute_: URL attribute to use to define the query
#Text=* _relation-types_: URIs of classes whose instances are relationships to reconcile
#Text=  * _ind-types_: classes that are instantiated by elements of this dimension.
#Text=* _rel2ind-predicates_: predicates connecting relations with elements of this dimension.
#Text=* _ind2dep-predicates_: predicates connecting elements of this dimension with potential dependencies.
#Text=* _preorder_: preorder to use for comparison on this dimension.
#Text=    * _Individuals_: preorder between individuals, must be specified:
#Text=      * _ind-leq-predicates_: list of predicates indicating that an individual is lower or equal than another.
#Text=* _ind-leq-predicates_: list of predciates indicating that an individual is greater or equal than another.
#Text=* _Annotations_: preorder based on annotations of individuals, must be specified:
#Text=      * _ann-base-uris_: prefixes of URIs of annotations to consider
#Text=      * _ind2ann-predicates_: predicates linking elements of this dimension to their annotations.
#Text=* _ann-leq-predicates_: predicates indicating that an annotation is lower or equal than another.
#Text=* _ann-geq-predicates_: predicates indicating that an annotation is greater or equal than another.
#Text=* _output-pred-equal_: URI of a predicate to use to identify equal relationships
#Text=* _output-pred-equiv_: URI of a predicate to use to identify equivalent relationships
#Text=* _output-pred-leq_: URI of a predicate to use to identify lower or equal relationships
#Text=* _output-pred-geq_: URI of a predicate to use to identify greater or equal relationships
#Text=* _output-pred-comparable_: URI of a predicate to use to identify comparable relationships
#Text=* _output-do-related-predicate_: URI of a predicate to use to identify relationships that are related
#Text=A [test/pgxo+test.owl](test/pgxo+test.owl) file is available to test tcn3r.
#Text=It should be imported in a triplestore.
#Text=After the import, run tcn3r using the test configuration provided in [test/test-conf.json](test/test-conf.json) and the following parameters
#Text=You may need to adapt ``server-address`` depending on the location of the triplestore you use.
#Text=The description of the test cases can be found in [test/documentation-tests.pdf](test/documentation-tests.pdf).
#Text=The (sorted) expected results can be found in [test/expected-output.ttl](test/expected-output.ttl).
